1. Under the general endotracheal anesthesia , the patient was placed at the surgical
table by supine position with hyperextended neck .
2. The operative field was prepared and drapped as usual sterile manner .
3. Low transverse curvilinear skin incision was made along the natural skin crease .

The flap was elevated upto the hyoid bone and inferiorly down to clavicle and manubrium . Posteriorly to trapezius muscle , the flap was developed . The lateral neck lymph node was dissected .
The thyroidal gland was mobilized from the trachea . The medial portion of the thyroid gland was clmped with mosquitos and the ipsilateral lobe was pused toward medially . 5. Superior thyroidal vessels were divided and ligated individually .
6. The thyroid gland was mobilized from the trachea . Inferior thyroid vessels were divided and ligated with identification and preservation of recurrent laryngeal nerve . The exposed tracheo - esophageal groove area was dissected with caution not to injure recurrent laryngeal nerve . Pretracheal portion of thyroid gland was dissected shaved out from the tracheal carilage . After delivery of the specimen , bleeders were controlled .
7. The dead space was irrigated with saline and minor bleeders were controlled . 8. The ribbon muscle was repaired with 3-0 vicryl interruptedly .
10. The platysma muscle and subcutaneous tissue were approximated with 3-0 vicryl interruptedly .
11. The skin was approximated by subcuticular continuous suture .
12. Aseptic dressing was applied on the operative wound .
